Mediathek
------------------------------------

Version: 1.0
Author: Nils HÃ¶rrmann (post@nilshoerrmann.de)
Build Date: 11th January 2009
Requirements: Symphony 2.0


[INSTALLATION]

1. Upload the 'mediathek' folder in this archive to your Symphony 'extensions' folder.

2. Enable it by selecting the "Field: Mediathek", choose Enable from the with-selected menu, then click Apply.

3. You can now add the "Mediathek" field to your sections.


[REQUIREMENTS]

- Requires latest Symphony revision from Github.

- A section containing an upload field that is used as media center resource.


[USAGE]

1. Upload files to your image or document section.

2. Move to your articles section with the "Mediathek" field


[NOTE]

- This is experimental code. Do not use this field in live environment!

- Currently this field does not allow data source grouping or table sorting.